yingyinNormal.en: So we should leave in about an hour. What is this "we"? I have to go and register Joe for the winter camp.
yingyinNormal.zh: 所以我们一小时后出发。什么"我们"？我得去给乔注册冬令营。

yingyinNormal.en: Come on! It's my wedding. That could be my present! Hey, I just gave you peeing on a stick. See, this is why you register.
yingyinNormal.zh: 快说吧，这是我的婚礼，你可以当做是送我的礼物。我刚刚答应为了你验孕。看吧，这就是你注册结婚的原因。

yingyinNormal.en: When I get married I'm going to register at the UCLA Cadaver Lab.
yingyinNormal.zh: 等我结婚，我要去洛杉矶加州大学尸体实验室登记礼物。

yingyinNormal.en: We don't have to wait in line and try so hard, cost so much to just pay to register.

yingyinNormal.en: Well, I don't know what that is, but it's got "coin" in it, and my cash register doesn't, so yeah.

word_usage.usage: register和enroll做动词都可以表示登记，register 一般是指录取后登记，或结婚的登记；而enroll是报名参加的登记，仅是报名阶段。
register表“注册、登记”时可及物也可不及物，登记某事是register for sth.，而向某人登记是register with sb.。

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: 意为“登记、注册”，指正式记录，列入目录、名单之中，并不一定要成为其中的一员，只强调有记录在案。
指正式成为某组织、群体的一员。
